<h3>Comments</h3>

<p>ANALYSIS OF MAIN THESES: Confucius taught that honest,
respectful, humble living ought to be each person's goal. Respect
your elders, in life and death; learn from them of the past and
adhere to tradition. </p>

<p> QUESTION# 3: What, according to Confucius, is wisdom?
Confucius said: &quot;...when you know a thing, say that you know
it; when you do not know a thing, admit you do not know it. That
is wisdom.&quot; </p>

<p> - I couldn't think of any way of restating it, so I copied it
verbatim from the book. </p>
